      children: "Mesut Aytunca, one of the most influential figures in Turkish rock music, founded his own band with Erol Bilem. After some line-up changes, Ber\xE7 K\xFCrk\xE7\xFC, Koray Y\u0131lmaz and Muzaffer G\xFCler joined them and they formed the band Sil\xFCetler in the early \u201960s. The band was heavily influenced by British instrumental rock band The Shadows, even in their choice of name. Sil\xFCetler were known for their rock\u2019n\u2019roll versions of Turkish folk songs, such as \xDCsk\xFCdar and Lorke. Sis, an instrumental piece, was the B-side of Ka\u015F\u0131k Havas\u0131, which came third in The Golden Microphone contest. This single was released in 1965 by H\xFCrriyet, the newspaper that organized the contest. The band released 4 singles and 1 LP until 1967. After two of the band members left the band and joined Mo\u011Follar, Aytunca worked with different members and released a solo single but Sil\xFCetler eventually came to an end in 1973. Aytunca was found dead in 1976."
