  title: 'Erkut Taçkın & Okan Dinçer ve Kontrastları - Özlem (1968)',
  image: './posters/erkut-tackin-okan-dincer-ve-kontrastları-ozlem.jpg',
  info: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("div", {
    className: "content-capsule",
    children: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
      children: "One of the first representatives of Turkish rock music, Erkut Ta\xE7k\u0131n started his career during his pupilage with Naval Military College Band. Ta\xE7k\u0131n who went to Germany as a factoy worker in 1962, couldn\u2019t stay away from music and joined the band named Black Point. The band\u2019s name changed to Erkut Ta\xE7k\u0131n and Durul Gence Quintet. After making music in Germany for a while, the band turned back to Turkey and became a pioneer of beat music. Ta\xE7k\u0131n joined the band, Okan Din\xE7er and Kontrastlar in 1968 and released M\xFCh\xFCr G\xF6zl\xFCm including the single named \xD6zlem."
    }, void 0, false, {
