  title: 'Korkut Koray - Yalnızlar Rıhtımı (1969)',
  image: './posters/korkut-koray-yalnizlar-rihtimi.jpg',
  info: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("div", {
    className: "content-capsule",
    children: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
      children: "Korkut Koray is the younger brother and the biggest supporter of Erkin Koray, one of the major figures in Turkish psychedelic music and Anatolian rock by the late 1960\u2019s. He started his music career with his brother\u2019s band, Erkin Koray and the Rhythm Makers. He earned a reputation as the first rock drummer of Turkey, and then turned the wheel hard to Latin music, and played with some orchestras. His trademark is to be able to play drums and to sing simultaneously. He released two 45\u2019s in the 1970\u2019s, and one of those is Arabac\u0131/Yaln\u0131zlar R\u0131ht\u0131m\u0131."
    }, void 0, false, {
