}, {
  title: 'Kaygısızlar - Şaşırdım (1969)',
  image: './posters/kaygisizlar-sasirdım.jpg',
  info: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("div", {
    className: "content-capsule",
    children: /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
      children: "Kayg\u0131s\u0131zlar were formed in 1965 by Fuat G\xFCner, Ender Arol and Semih Aksoy. Shortly after, Fuat G\xFCner met Mazhar Alanson and asked him to join the band. They went through some lineup changes and finally, in 1967, they met with Bar\u0131\u015F Man\xE7o. They released 8 singles together, which were deeply influenced by beat music and psychedelic rock. Their first single without Bar\u0131\u015F Man\xE7o, \u201C\u015Ea\u015F\u0131rd\u0131m / Son Gece\u201D was released in 1969 by Sayan label. \u201C\u015Ea\u015F\u0131rd\u0131m\u201D was an interpretation of the song \u201CShort Circuit\u201D by the rock band The ID. After releasing 3 more singles, the band split in 1971."
    }, void 0, false, {
