      children: "Aziz Azmet was born in 1947. He started his music career in the band Meteorlar. In 1967, he joined Sil\xFCetler along with Murat Ses. The same year, the band released their one and only LP, which mostly consisted of covers of popular English songs. Later that year, Aziz Azmet and Murat Ses left the band and formed Mo\u011Follar, which went on to become one of the most popular Turkish bands. Not satisfied with the band\u2019s musical direction, Azmet left Mo\u011Follar in 1970 and released 3 solo singles. Hi\xE7 \u0130stemem was the B-side of his first single, Beni Yaln\u0131z B\u0131rakma, released by Diskot\xFCr label. After working with 3 H\xFCrel for a short time, Aziz Azmet put an end to his musical life."
